cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this environment in research, please cite it as below."
title: "Wildfire Dispatch Environment for OpenEnv"
abstract: >
  A high-fidelity AI evaluation environment that simulates wildfire resource
  dispatch under life-or-death pressure. Tests whether language models can
  prioritize human lives over political noise, manage hidden threats via
  multi-step investigation, and make split-second triage decisions under
  resource scarcity. Built for the OpenEnv specification with 3 difficulty
  levels, deterministic graders producing scores in [0.0, 1.0], and verified
  baseline results from Mistral Large.
